.TH "drm_vblank_restore" 9 "drm_vblank_restore" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
drm_vblank_restore \- estimate missed vblanks and update vblank count.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" drm_vblank_restore
.BI "(struct drm_device *dev "  ","
.BI "unsigned int pipe "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dev" 12
DRM device
.IP "pipe" 12
CRTC index
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Power manamement features can cause frame counter resets between vblank
disable and enable. Drivers can use this function in their
\fIdrm_crtc_funcs.enable_vblank\fP implementation to estimate missed vblanks since
the last \fIdrm_crtc_funcs.disable_vblank\fP using timestamps and update the
vblank counter.

This function is the legacy version of \fBdrm_crtc_vblank_restore\fP.
